<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="62" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="9" pageNumber="62">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="9" pageNumber="62">
The species was previously described based on male specimens from Jiangxi Prov., and this is the first record of its female. The male of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Derops" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Derops schillhammeri" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schillhammeri">Derops schillhammeri</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken originalValue="Schülke">Schuelke</normalizedToken>
previously known from Jiangxi Prov., China. It is very similar to 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Derops" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Derops shuckburghae" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="shuckburghae">Derops shuckburghae</taxonomicName>
Rougemont, from Thailand (
<bibRefCitation pageId="9" pageNumber="62">Rougemont 2003</bibRefCitation>
: 998-999, plate 1, 2 (figs 1, 3-6, 8)). Females may be easily distinguished by the depth of tergite VIII emargination almost half of itself and not very broad apices.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
